r fewer times when those few hundred hitpoints have been the difference between life and death. <br>
<br>
At my level now (and for most of the life of my mage) if I've lost half my hitpoints I'll probably be losing them all anyways. I either don't get aggro (for example I'm usually one of the last people to die in a raid), or if I have it's already too late for ANY amount of hitpoints to save me.<br>
<br>
In my opinion max your Int as it will help the most at lower levels, and even at high levels it lets you switch out Int gear earlier for nicer items if you want to. I'd then put the rest into Str. <br>
<br>
When it comes to high level game though, any stat can be raised easily, so raise the stats that will help you most pre 50. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ashua>Ashua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 10:50:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> First thing if you want the agil AC bonus then you must take it to 76 (there is no bonus at 75).<br>
